tell me about the report over 3 years

The report over the past three years for Michael Anderson shows a series of laboratory results and physician remarks indicating his health status from 2024 to 2026.

In 2024, Michael's test results were all within normal ranges, with a hemoglobin level of 13.5 g/dL, white blood cell (WBC) count of 7,200 /uL, platelet count of 220,000 /uL, and glucose level of 92 mg/dL. The doctor noted that all parameters were within normal range (Source 5: Michael_Anderson_3_Year_Scanned_Report.pdf, Page 0).

In 2025, there was a mild elevation in glucose to 108 mg/dL, which prompted the doctor to advise monitoring his diet. His hemoglobin was at 12.8 g/dL, WBC count was slightly higher at 8,100 /puL, and platelets were at 205,000 /uL (Source 4: Michael_Anderson_3_Year_Scanned_Report.pdf, Page 1).

By 2026, Michael's health indicators showed improvement. His hemoglobin increased to 14.1 g/dL, WBC count normalized to 6,900 /uL, platelets rose to 240,000 /uL, and glucose decreased to 95 mg/dL. The doctor remarked on the stabilization of values and noted good improvement (Source 2: Michael_Anderson_3_Year_Scanned_Report.pdf, Page 2).

Overall, the reports over the three years indicate a positive trend in Michael Anderson's health, with improvements particularly noted in the most recent year.
